income3 = dagitty("dag{
                 Education -> Income
                 }")

coordinates(income3) = list(x = c(Education = 1, Income = 2),
                          y = c(Education = 1, Income = 1))
plot(income3)

Confounding variables are considered in the randomized treatment as everything is set same in two groups except the education. The different in result must be attributed to education.



